&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Senior Cloud Systems Administrator to join a team dedicated to maintaining and optimizing mission-critical information technology (IT) infrastructure. In this role, you will design, deploy, automate, and maintain cloud infrastructure and Linux-based environments using AWS, Kubernetes, Terraform, and Ansible. The ideal candidate for this position will have extensive experience administering Linux-based cloud environments and automating infrastructure along with an IAT Level II or higher certification. Please consider applying if you meet the following qualifications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;TS/SCI with polygraph security clearance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Bachelor of Science (B.S.) degree&amp;nbsp;in a technical discipline and ten (10) years of relevant experience is required. In lieu of a degree, fifteen (15) years of experience as a System Administrator performing relevant job functions is acceptable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;DoD 8570 Information Assurance Technical (IAT) Level II certification or higher.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience implementing, administering, troubleshooting, and maintaining enterprise IT systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience administering Linux/UNIX operating systems, including installation, configuration, patching, and maintenance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience automating infrastructure provisioning and configuration using Terraform and Ansible.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience administering AWS cloud infrastructure and cloud-native services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

